				by the <token>FSF</token>.
			</para>
		</introduction>

		<section>
			<content>
				<list class="bullet">
					<listItem>
						<para>
							The published <token>COM</token> interfaces (and associated <token>PIAs</token>) are covered by the
							<token>LGPL3</token>.
						</para>
						<list class="bullet">
							<listItem>
								<para>
									This is the license that covers the use of libraries within an application. Using a <token>COM</token> interface or <token>PIA</token> is functionally equivalent
									to dynamically binding to a runtime library.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									The <token>COM</token> interfaces and <token>PIAs</token>
									covered by this licence include all interfaces for the Agent Control and Agent Server.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									The intention is to allow any application that uses <token>MsAgent</token>'s published
									<token>COM</token> interfaces to use Double Agent in the same way.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									The GNU <legacyBold>Lesser</legacyBold> General Public License licence allows any application, including <phrase>proprietary</phrase>
									applications, to use open source libraries, with the proper prominent acknowledgement and references
									to the open source.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									The easiest way provide acknowledgement is to provide access to the Double Agent copyright page. The
									sample source code in the Double Agent project includes examples of application <ui>About</ui> boxes
									that do this.
								</para>
							</listItem>
						</list>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							The rest of Double Agent (i.e. the internals) is covered by the <token>GPL3</token>.
						</para>
						<list class="bullet">
							<listItem>
								<para>
									This license restricts usage to <phrase>non-proprietary</phrase> applications. A <phrase>proprietary</phrase> application
									may not bind to these libraries either statically (at build time) or dynamically (at run time).
									A <phrase>proprietary</phrase> application must not make use of any Double Agent source code or
									<phrase>any derivation of it</phrase>.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									The intention is to restrict usage of any portion Double Agent that is not available through the published
									<token>COM</token> interfaces and <token>PIAs</token> interfaces.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									A <phrase>non-proprietary</phrase> application that binds to any portion of Double Agent other than the published
									<token>COM</token> interfaces and <token>PIAs</token> interfaces
									must include the appropriate acknowledgements and references, and must itself conform to the GNU General
									Public License or an acceptable alternative.
								</para>
							</listItem>
						</list>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>For Double Agent version 1.2 this specifically means:</para>
						<list class="bullet">
							<listItem>
								<para>
									The basic Double Agent installation available on the <externalLink>
										<linkText>SourceForge</linkText>
										<linkUri>http://sourceforge.net/projects/doubleagent/files/</linkUri>
									</externalLink> website is sufficient for any application.&#160; The development and debugging
									components are not required at runtime.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									Any application may use the <token>COM</token> interfaces defined in
									<localUri>DaControl.tlb</localUri> and <localUri>DaControlOdl.h</localUri> and implemented by
									<localUri>DaControl.dll</localUri>.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									Any application may use the <token>COM</token> interfaces defined in <localUri>DaServer.tlb</localUri>
									and <localUri>DaServerOdl.h</localUri> and implemented by <localUri>DaServer.exe</localUri>.
								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									Any application may use the <token>PIAs</token> implemented by <localUri>DoubleAgent.Control.dll</localUri>, <localUri>DoubleAgent.AxControl.dll</localUri>,
									and <localUri>DoubleAgent.Server.dll</localUri>.

								</para>
							</listItem>
							<listItem>
								<para>
									Everything else is restricted to <legacyItalic>non-proprietary</legacyItalic> applications.
								</para>
							</listItem>
						</list>
					</listItem>
				</list>
				<para/>
			</content>
